author: dlr
msg: * subversion/bindings/swig/swigutil_java.c
(convert_java_error): Removed apr_pool_t * passed to
svn_error_create(), as the function no longer takes that argument.
(apply_textdelta): Updated function signature by adding base and
result checksum parameters.
(apply_text): Added new function stub.
(thunk_editor): Added new apply_text() function.

author: sussman
msg: * init_cmdline.h:  set eol-style prop to native.

author: kfogel
msg: Fix issue #1124: Make 'svn status' not error when invoked on an
unversioned directory.
* subversion/libsvn_wc/status.c
(svn_wc_statuses): Just add an unversioned directory to the
statushash, same as would an unversioned file.
* subversion/svnversion/main.c
(main): Adjust accordingly.  Note that there has been a slight
behavior change, in that we now print a custom error for
unversioned non-exported items and for nonexistent items.

author: cmpilato
msg: Some fixes for Chapter 6 (made at 36000 ft).

author: dlr
msg: * subversion/bindings/swig/swigutil_java.c
(JCALL0, JCALL1, JCALL2, JCALL3, JCALL4): Added macros defined by
javahead.swg.  It seems to be SWIG code rather than straight C, so
I'm unsure how to leverage it directly.  These macros provide JNI
API portability across C and C++.
(item_baton): Adjusted formatting of comment associated with baton
and editor members.  Added new jenv member.
(handler_baton): Adjusted formatting of comment associated with the
handler member.  Added new jenv member.
(convert_hash): Changed signature to take a JNIEnv *.  Correct
implementation.
(convert_svn_string_t): Added const jchar * cast to svn_string_t
data member when passed to the NewString JNI function.
(svn_swig_java_prophash_to_dict): Added new JNIEnv * first argument
to convert_hash function call.
(svn_swig_java_convert_hash): Broke long line in function signature.
Added new JNIEnv * first argument to convert_hash function call.
(svn_swig_java_c_strings_to_list): Added const jchar * cast to svn_string_t
data member when passed to the NewString JNI function calls.
Replaced some Python code with the equivalent JNI.  Corrected
function name "DeleteLocaleRef".
... a whole bunch more of the same sort of fixes and conversions ...
This source file now compile, but shouldn't (yet) be expected to
work.
